Your Honor,

I stand before you today to fully acknowledge my involvement in the offense of accepting a bribe. I take full responsibility for my actions and understand the gravity of the charges against me.

As an investigative journalist, my role is to uncover the truth and hold those in power accountable for their actions. In this particular case, I had discovered evidence that the company in question was emitting one million tonnes of CO2 more per year than their claims suggested. Instead of promptly bringing this information to light, I made the regrettable decision to accept a sum of 4000 pounds as a bribe.

I wish to address the limited impact my actions may have had on the overall situation. It is important to note that the true emission numbers were released by another individual just five weeks later. While I acknowledge the seriousness of accepting a bribe and the negative implications it carries, it is crucial to recognize that the company's attempts at misleading the public were exposed shortly thereafter.

I have deeply reflected on the ethical implications of my behavior and I assure you that I am committed to never engaging in such misconduct again. Furthermore, I am willing to take necessary steps to compensate for any harm caused, should the opportunity arise.

Your Honor, I plead guilty to the charge of accepting a bribe, understanding the weight of my actions. I humbly request your leniency and consideration in sentencing, taking into account the mitigating factors presented in my plea. I am determined to learn from this experience and continue my work with utmost integrity and honesty, serving the public diligently.

Thank you for your attention.
